      {
        "id": 372877,
        "name": null,
        "username": "Battler",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/battler/{size}/208_2.png",
        "created_at": "2012-02-29T14:22:12.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Lawrence\" data-post=\"8\" data-topic=\"13984\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"//forum.magicball.net/user_avatar/localhost/lawrence/48/607_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Lawrence:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Well, I have another problem now I cant edit those commands at all. LBA Scene Editor is horribly bugged, for example: I delete an actors life script and paste in a new one that is different, save the changes, check again the script and for some odd reason the original script is STILL there, except garbled up with a few characters from the script I pasted in (which makes the game crash)<br>\nIs there any tool that actually works that lets me edit actor scripts? <img src=\"//forum.magicball.net/plugins/discourse-lba-emoji/images/takam/frowning_face.png?v=12\" title=\":frowning_face:\" class=\"emoji emoji-custom\" alt=\":frowning_face:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Yes of course, the script part of the released version of the LBA Scene Manager is very buggy. Im working on an improvement (Ive also PMd Zink about the LBA 2 script commands) but I have no idea on how much its going to take.</p>",
